---
import AnimatedSection from '../ui/AnimatedSection.astro';
---

<AnimatedSection animation="fade-up" delay={100}>
  <section
    class="px-6 md:px-16 py-section border-t border-ink"
    aria-labelledby="instructor-bio-heading"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase opacity-40 mb-6">
      Instructor
    </p>

    <h2
      id="instructor-bio-heading"
      class="text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] mb-16 max-w-4xl"
    >
      Alvin Penaflor
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] mb-6">
          16 Years of Lapunti Arnis de Abanico
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-60">
          Alvin Penaflor has dedicated sixteen years to the study and practice
          of Lapunti Arnis de Abanico — a Filipino martial art defined by
          fluid, fan-like striking patterns and precise footwork. His training
          began under direct instruction from senior practitioners within the
          Lapunti lineage, grounding him in the technical rigor and cultural
          depth that the system demands.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-60 mt-4">
          Over the course of his practice, Alvin has trained across multiple
          formats — solo drilling, partner work, and live sparring — developing
          a comprehensive understanding of the system's principles at every
          level of application. His progression reflects not just accumulated
          hours, but a deliberate commitment to understanding the "why" behind
          each technique.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] mb-6">
          Teaching Philosophy
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-60">
          Alvin approaches instruction the same way he approaches software
          engineering: with a bias toward first principles. Before a student
          learns a technique, they learn the principle that generates it.
          This makes the art transferable — a student who understands the
          governing logic of Lapunti can adapt under pressure, not just
          replicate patterns in a controlled environment.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-60 mt-4">
          His classes and seminars are structured to be accessible to
          beginners while remaining technically demanding for experienced
          practitioners. The goal is not to produce students who can perform
          — it is to produce students who can think, adapt, and carry the
          tradition forward with integrity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 border-t border-ink pt-16 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
      <div>
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05]">16</p>
        <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase opacity-40 mt-2">Years of Practice</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05]">1</p>
        <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase opacity-40 mt-2">System Mastered</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05]">PH</p>
        <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase opacity-40 mt-2">Filipino Lineage</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05]">∞</p>
        <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase opacity-40 mt-2">Ongoing Study</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</AnimatedSection>
